Same-sex marriage is under [[Same-sex union legislation|consideration by the legislature]] or the courts in the [[Recognition of same-sex unions in the Czech Republic|Czech Republic]],<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/politics/short_news/czech-president-will-veto-same-sex-marriage-bill-if-lawmakers-approve-it/ | title=Czech president will veto same-sex marriage bill if lawmakers approve it | date=8 June 2022}}</ref> [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Greece|Greece]],<ref>''Cyprus Digest'', [https://cyprus-digest.com/marriage-for-loatki-couples-the-syriza-bill-was-submitted-what-does-it-provide-for-childbearing/ Marriage for LOATKI + couples: The SYRIZA bill was submitted – What does it provide for childbearing] June 19, 2022</ref> [[LGBT rights in Honduras|Honduras]],<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.latribuna.hn/2022/05/18/presentaran-iniciativa-de-ley-para-que-el-matrimonio-igualitario-sea-legal-en-honduras/ | title=Presentarán iniciativa de ley para que el matrimonio igualitario sea legal en Honduras | date=18 May 2022 }}</ref> [[Recognition of same-sex unions in India|India]],<ref>{{cite web |date=2022-04-02 |title=NCP's Supriya Sule brings Bill to legalise same-sex marriage |website=The Indian Express |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/ncps-supriya-sule-brings-bill-to-legalise-same-sex-marriage-7848768/ |access-date=2022-04-02}}</ref> [[Same-sex marriage in Liechtenstein|Liechtenstein]],<ref>{{cite web | url=https://twitter.com/LGBTMarriage/status/1587852184925806592 | title= }}</ref> the [[LGBT rights in the Navajo Nation|Navajo Nation]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.daily-times.com/story/news/local/navajo-nation/2022/03/23/delegates-sponsor-bill-legalize-same-sex-marriage-navajo-nation/7135151001/ |title=Delegates sponsor bill to legalize same-sex marriage on Navajo Nation |publisher=Daily-times.com |date= |accessdate=2022-05-14}}</ref> [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Peru|Peru]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elcomercio.pe/politica/congreso/congreso-de-la-republica-presentan-proyecto-de-ley-sobre-el-matrimonio-igualitario-entre-personas-del-mismo-sexo-juntos-por-el-peru-somos-peru-partido-morado-nndc-noticia/?ref=ecr |title=Presentan proyecto de ley sobre el matrimonio igualitario entre personas del mismo sexo |publisher=elcomercio.pe |date=23 October 2021|accessdate=2022-06-28}}</ref> [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Thailand|Thailand]]<ref name=thailand>{{cite web|url= https://www.thaipbsworld.com/house-panel-allows-same-sex-foreign-couples-to-register-civil-partnership-in-thailand/ |title= House panel allows same-sex foreign couples to register civil partnership in Thailand |date=27 July 2022 |access-date=27 July 2022 |archive-date= |archive-url= |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Venezuela|Venezuela]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://elacarigueno.com/ini/diputada-plantea-iniciativa-para-el-matrimonio-civil-igualitario-en-la-asamblea-nacional/|title= Diputada plantea iniciativa para el matrimonio civil igualitario en la Asamblea Nacional|work=El Acarigueño|date=24 February 2022|language=es}}</ref>

[[Civil union]]s are being considered in a number of countries, including [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Lithuania|Lithuania]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Lithuanian MPs propose civil union as compromise on same-sex partnership |url=https://www.baltictimes.com/lithuanian_mps_propose_civil_union_as_compromise_on_same-sex_partnership/ |access-date=2022-05-23 |website=www.baltictimes.com}}</ref> [[Recognition of same-sex unions in the Philippines|the Philippines]],<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/topstories/nation/841251/padilla-wants-same-sex-unions-institutionalized/story/ | title=Padilla wants same-sex unions institutionalized }}</ref> [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Serbia|Serbia]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://javnerasprave.euprava.gov.rs/javna-rasprava/257 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208080841/http://javnerasprave.euprava.gov.rs/javna-rasprava/257 |archive-date=2021-02-08 |url-status=dead |title=Јавне консултације за израду текста Нацрта закона о истополним заједницама}}</ref> [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Thailand|Thailand]]<ref name=thailand/> and [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Ukraine|Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web| title= Zelensky responded to the petition on the legalization of same-sex marriages in Ukraine.|author= Anna Kholodnova |date= 2 August 2022 |website= Бабель |url= https://babel.ua/en/news/82388-zelensky-responded-to-the-petition-on-the-legalization-of-same-sex-marriages-in-ukraine}}</ref>

On 12 March 2015, the [[European Parliament]] passed a non-binding resolution encouraging EU institutions and member states to "[reflect] on the recognition of same-sex marriage or same-sex civil union as a political, social and human and civil rights issue".<ref>{{cite web|title=UKIP and Tories abstain on EU motion to recognise same-sex marriage|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/03/13/ukip-and-tories-abstain-on-eu-motion-to-recognise-same-sex-marriage/ |access-date=26 July 2015|website=PinkNews|date=13 March 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150809064225/http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/03/13/ukip-and-tories-abstain-on-eu-motion-to-recognise-same-sex-marriage/ |archive-date=9 August 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Texts adopted – Thursday, 12 March 2015 – Annual report on human rights and democracy in the world 2013 and the EU policy on the matter |publisher=European Parliament |url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/sides/getDoc.do?pubRef=-//EP//TEXT+TA+P8-TA-2015-0076+0+DOC+XML+V0//EN&language=EN|access-date=26 July 2015|archive-date=7 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150807122729/http://www.europarl.europa.eu/sides/getDoc.do?pubRef=-%2F%2FEP%2F%2FTEXT+TA+P8-TA-2015-0076+0+DOC+XML+V0%2F%2FEN&language=EN|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Annual report on human rights and democracy in the world 2013 and the EU policy on the matter|website=Vote Watch Europe|url=http://www.votewatch.eu/en/term8-annual-report-on-human-rights-and-democracy-in-the-world-2013-and-the-eu-policy-on-the-matter-motion-8.html |access-date=26 July 2015|archive-date=8 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150508143007/http://www.votewatch.eu/en/term8-annual-report-on-human-rights-and-democracy-in-the-world-2013-and-the-eu-policy-on-the-matter-motion-8.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2018, the [[Inter-American Court of Human Rights]] ruled that all signatory countries must allow same-sex marriage.

Notable countries:

* {{Flagicon|United States}} United States: The first local jurisdiction to knowingly issue a marriage license to a same-sex couple (1971)
* {{Flagicon|Denmark}} Denmark: The first country to offer civil unions (1989)
* {{Flagicon|Netherlands}} Netherlands: The first country to legalize same-sex marriage, and the first European one (2001)
* {{Flagicon|Canada}} Canada: The first American country to legalize same-sex marriage (2005)
* {{Flagicon|South Africa}} South Africa: The first country to legalize same-sex marriage through court ruling and the first African one (2005)
* {{Flagicon|Mexico}} Mexico: The first local jurisdiction to legalize same-sex marriage in Latin America (2010)
* {{Flagicon|Argentina}} Argentina: The first South American country to legalize same-sex marriage (2010)
* {{Flagicon|New Zealand}} New Zealand: The first Oceanian country to legalize same-sex marriage (2013)
* {{Flagicon|Ireland}} Ireland: The first country to legalize same-sex marriage through referendum (2015)
* {{Flagicon|Taiwan}} Taiwan: The first Asian country to legalize same-sex marriage (2019)
* {{Flagicon|Cuba}} Cuba: The first [[one-party state]] to legalize same-sex marriage (2022)<ref>{{cite news|date=3 October 2022|title=How the Chinese internet saw Cuba's vote on gay marriage, surrogacy|newspaper=South China Morning Post|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3194582/how-chinese-internet-saw-cubas-vote-gay-marriage-surrogacy|access-date=17 October 2022}}</ref>

In response to the international spread of same-sex marriage, a number of countries have enacted preventative [[Same-sex union legislation#Bans|constitutional bans]], with the most recent being [[LGBT rights in Georgia (country)|Georgia]] in 2018 and [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Russia|Russia]] in 2020. In other countries, constitutions have been adopted which have wording specifying that marriage is between a man and a woman, although, especially with the older constitutions, they were not necessarily worded with the intent to ban same-sex marriage.{{citation needed|date=December 2021}}

